title: Reroutes even after I say no multiple times
text: Even after I say no/dimiss a ‚Äúbetter‚Äù route, the app will continue to offer to reroute me. Eventually I miss the prompt (because I am paying attention to the road) and it will reroute me without my consent. Often the ‚Äúbetter‚Äù route is $7-$20 more expensive and only save 1-2 minutes, but their ‚Äúbetter‚Äùalgorithm is relentless in a disrespectful and anti-user way. There is no toggle or control to ‚Äúauto decline‚Äù future re-routing prompts. There is no ‚Äúdo not reroute if route is more expensive ‚Äú control either. It‚Äôs an engineering-heavy feature that disregards user intent, and it‚Äôs dangerous to drivers who are expecting one route then suddenly find themselves elsewhere. Evil design.

title: Absurd alternative routes that distract
text: I used to rely on google maps as a primary navigation app but have noticed the app constantly loads ridiculous alternative routes that provide real no viable benefit and are distracting. The only reason an alternative should be presented if it saves time or equivalent reasonably - I don‚Äôt need 5 alternatives routes with options 45 mins longer. They also pop up constantly - a slower by 10 min route pops up and stays on screen until you pass it - annoying. It gets really hectic when 2-3 alternatives all equally bad - like getting off a freeway then back on only to loose 6 mins time and gain nothing but a busy screen. Also alternatives are not being informed by a traffic issue, where a detour could impart some benefit. Also - search along map doesn‚Äôt load past searches - like I have to type in-out burgers, which I‚Äôve searched for as a stop Tom many times to count. It loads past searches nowhere in vicinity - like a stop in a different not on my route - pointless.

title: Stop automatic rerouting!
text: I always look at my route options before I leave and choose the one I want based on whatever I‚Äôm feeling that day. Sometimes I want the most direct, sometimes I want something more scenic, sometimes I want to avoid certain areas or tolls. But unless I am watching the app like a hawk ‚Äî which I can‚Äôt because I‚ÄôM DRIVING ‚Äî it will automatically change my route without telling me. I appreciate it letting me know if something comes up like an accident, but don‚Äôt just change my route for the heck of it, and it should default to the route you chose originally and make you select the new one rather than the other way around. On my last long trip, I ended up on a toll road, which not only cost me money but wasn‚Äôt even the most direct route! it might be time to switch to Apple Maps because this is ridiculous.

title: Century 21 realty Broadway Columbia Mo
text: I contracted Chris Schmidt century 21 realtor Broadway Columbia. I found a house that I wanted to buy. Chris said that there were a lot of things that needed to be done in the house. He wanted to introduce me to his handyman who he‚Äôd known for years and trusted thoroughly. I hired the handyman to put a lining in a fence and move a toilet and that was it the day of my move. Chris did not meet me at the house and give them the keys to the new house. All I had was a garage door opener. I drove to my house to wait for the moving van. They put everything value in my house. I went back to the other house to clean it out met the realtor there. There were multiple people who had been given access to my house that I was unaware of there had been silver left on the bottom of my walk-in closet which was still there when I got to the house I put it in my purse when I got back to the house that I had purchased and just moved into. I found the handyman that Chris Schmidt had allowed access to my house with no one there. It turned out that, someone took a large box of silver flatware from 1917 and had been in my family for five generations. It was a little under $10,000. When I had put my purse on the kitchen counter I never saw my silver coins again the handyman had come in the house, I don‚Äôt know why he grabbed a hand drill that I had on the counter and said oh it doesn‚Äôt work and then left the house. I think he came in to steal the silver out of my purse. I think I was set up it was a crime of opportunity I am old, this person should‚Äôve never been let into my house by a realtor. The realtor should‚Äôve given me a key to have locked the house up in the very start of the day. He didn‚Äôt do this. He left me vulnerable I can‚Äôt prove it, but I know that my silver was stolen that day, my silver flatware and my silver coins, I would never use this realtor and I would never trust a handyman who has no tools he doesn‚Äôt have a weed whacker. He doesn‚Äôt have a broom on his truck. He doesn‚Äôt have any instruments to cut anything he has nothing. He just simply shows up on his truck with his old beat up mower. There aren‚Äôt any company signs on it. There aren‚Äôt any telephone numbers and I know that this guy goes into old women‚Äôs homes, introduced by Chris to do odd jobs. I would never never never recommend this realtor ever when you‚Äôre older your vulnerable. When I was busy cleaning out the old house I was being robbed from my new house I never had a Chance.

title: Outrage and Condemnation: Google‚Äôs Removal of Palestine from Maps
text:
Dear Google,

I am deeply troubled by your decision to remove Palestine from Google Maps. Innocent lives are being lost, and your actions appear to endorse the erasure of Palestine.

It is incomprehensible why such a choice would be made, and it feels like a betrayal of human rights and dignity. Know that your actions do not go unnoticed, and there is widespread outrage at this injustice.

Allah's wisdom surpasses human understanding, and justice will prevail in the end. Your actions will not go unaccounted for, and the consequences will be severe.

Sincerely disappointed, 
Hijas
